'''Freeman Cobb''' (1830–1878)<ref>[http://adbonline.anu.edu.au/biogs/A030404b.htm Biography of Cobb, Freeman]</ref> was an American, who established the [[Cobb and Co]] stagecoach company in 1853 with partners [[John Murray Peck]], [[James Scanlon]] and [[John B. Lamber]]. The company was based in [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Australia]], and ran American-imported Concord coaches to and from the Victorian goldfields. Cobb returned to the United States after three and a half years but associates continued operating under the name Cobb & Company. He had introduced the use of Concord coaches to Australia and built a brand so strong the companies operated it until 1924.  

