{{more citations needed|date=March 2015}} {{Infobox person <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] --> |name = Prodromos Bodosakis-Athanasiadis |image = Bodosakis-Athanasiadis Prodromos.jpg |caption = Prodromos Bodosakis-Athanasiadis |birth_date = {{birth-date|1890|1890}} |birth_place = [[Bor, Niğde|Bor, Cappadocia]], [[Ottoman Empire]] |death_date = 1979 |death_place = |residence = |citizenship = |nationality = |field = |work_institutions = |alma_mater = [[Industrialist]] |known_for = |footnotes = |signature = }}
'''Prodromos Bodosakis-Athanasiadis''' ({{lang-el|'''Πρόδρομος Μποδοσάκης Αθανασιάδης '''}}) (1890-1979) was one of the most important figures in 20th century [[Greece|Greek]] industrial history. He created an immense industrial empire with weapons factories, [[Mining|mines]] and plants in diverse branches of industry in the 1930s.<ref name=" Klemann 2013 ">{{cite book |title= Occupied Economies: An Economic History of Nazi-Occupied Europe, 1939-1945 |last= Klemann|first= Hein A.M. |year= 2013 |publisher= Berg|isbn=9780857850607 |quote= In the 1930s Prodromos Bodosakis-Athanasiadis created a huge industrial empire with arms factories, mines and plants in diverse branches of industry. |page= 353}}</ref>
==Early life== He was born to a [[Cappadocian Greeks|Cappadocian Greek]] family in the region of [[Bor, Niğde|Bor, Cappadocia]], [[Asia minor]] in 1890.<ref name=" Boinodiris 2010 ">{{cite book |title= Andros Odyssey: Liberation: (1900-1940) |last= Boinodiris |first= Stavros |year=2010 |publisher= iUniverse |isbn= 9781440193859 |quote= Prodromos Athanasiades-Bodosakis was born in Bohr, Cappadocia. After the exchange of populations he became a Greek industrialist who in 1934 took over Pyrkal, an armament company and one of the oldest defense industries. |page=22 }}</ref> Prodomos migrated to Greece after the [[Greco-Turkish War (1919–22)]]. From 1934, he controlled the [[Pyrkal]], one of the oldest Greek defence industries with significant contribution during the [[Greco-Italian War]].
