'''Syed Alamgir''' is a [[Bangladesh]]i business executive. He is renowned for incorporating the [[halal]] concept in the [[FMCG]] category. Presently{{when|date=November 2018}}, he is working for [[ACI Limited]] as Managing Director.

==Education==
Syed Alamgir was born on 1 August 1951. He completed his Masters in Business Administration (MBA) from the [[Institute of Business Administration, University of Dhaka]] in 1976. He obtained his Ph.D from University of New Castle, [[Oregon, USA]].

==Career==
He started career in British Pharmaceutical Company [[May & Baker]] (currently [[Sanofi Aventis]]) in 1976. He also worked in Pegasus Shoes, Jamuna Knitting and Dyeing, Aromatic Cosmetics Ltd.<ref name="ibtbd">{{cite web|url=http://ibtbd.net/syed-alamgir-managing-director-aci-consumer-brands/|title=Syed Alamgir, Managing Director, ACI Consumer Brands - ICE Business Times|website=ibtbd.net|accessdate=2018-10-30}}</ref>

He was the pioneer of concept of 100% halal soap in Bangladesh toiletries industry. Professor [[Philip Kotler]] has mentioned the positioning of 100% halal soap idea in his Principles of Marketing book.<ref>in 13th edition of ‘Principles of Marketing 13th Edition – A South Asian Perspective’ 2010 (page 76)</ref>

He is serving as President of [[Bangladesh Vacuum Salt Manufacturers’ Association]], [[Bangladesh Sanitary Napkin & Diapers Manufacturers’ Association]], [[MBA Association of Bangladesh]], [[Bangladesh-Greece Chamber of Commerce and Industry (BGCCI)]].<ref name="observerbd">{{cite web|url=http://www.observerbd.com/details.php?id=130974|title=Managing Director of ACI Consumer Brands - Business|website=observerbd.com|accessdate=2018-10-30}}</ref>

For his contribution as a business leader, in October 2018 he has been selected as an advisory of [[United Nation]] board member for Bangladesh of.<ref name="youtube">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TwXYGSszbJY|title=I Style with Dr. Syed Alamgir independent television|website=YouTube|accessdate=2018-10-30}}</ref>

==Personal life==

Syed Alamgir is married to Popy Akter and is the father of three daughters.

==Awards==
* Best Marketing Director by Rapport Bangladesh in 2002
* Retail Person of the Year award in the Asian Retail Congress in 2014

